paragraphs.text:
%python
from binance.client import Client
from pprint import pprint as p
from datetime import datetime
import numpy as np
import time
import pandas as pd

def __Api__():
    f = open("/home/scio/zepl/conf/API_KEY", 'r')
    line = f.readline()
    f.close()
    return line
def __Sign__():
    f = open("/home/scio/zepl/conf/SECRET_KEY", 'r')
    line = f.readline()
    f.close()
    return line

paragraphs.title: GET 4Klines and To json
paragraphs.text:
%python
BTC='BTCUSDT'
client = Client(__Api__(),__Sign__())
klines_orig = client.get_historical_klines(BTC, '4h', "1 Jul, 2014")

for i in range(len(klines_orig)):
    # klines_orig[i][0]=datetime.fromtimestamp(klines_orig[i][0]/1000).strftime('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M')
    # klines_orig[i][6]=datetime.fromtimestamp(klines_orig[i][6]/1000).strftime('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M')
    klines_orig[i][0]=int(datetime.fromtimestamp(klines_orig[i][0]/1000).strftime('%Y%m%d%H%M'))
    klines_orig[i][6]=int(datetime.fromtimestamp(klines_orig[i][6]/1000).strftime('%Y%m%d%H%M'))
klines=np.array(klines_orig)
# klines=klines[:,1:6]

df=pd.DataFrame(klines)
with open("/home/scio/Desktop/bot/data/4klines.json", 'w') as f:
    f.write(df.to_json(orient='records', lines=True))
df.to_csv("/home/scio/Desktop/bot/data/4klines.csv",sep=',')
print("shape is",klines.shape)
